<p>Before diving into the trading world, it’s crucial to have a solid grasp of what cryptocurrencies are, how blockchain technology works, and the underlying principles behind digital assets. Start by understanding key concepts like decentralization, mining, and smart contracts, and get familiar with popular cryptocurrencies such as Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), and newer ones emerging in 2025.</p>
  
<h3>1.1 Resources for Learning the Basics</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Online Courses:</strong> Platforms like Coursera, Udemy, and Binance Academy offer free or paid courses that provide detailed overviews of blockchain and crypto fundamentals.</li>
